                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17863927" author="knoguchi" created="Mon, 8 Jul 2024 20:27:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; &quot;Implementing class java.lang.IncompatibleClassChangeError: Implementing class&quot;&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This error was coming from incompatible mockito version. &quot;&lt;br/&gt;
Pig using mockito 1.8.4, Hadoop-3.3.6 using mockito 2.28.2.&#160;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Uploading the patch which upgrades hadoop and tez, pulls the new dependencies and updates test that uses alternative Whitebox implementation provided in Hadoop which went away as part of the mockito upgrade.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17863929" author="rohini" created="Mon, 8 Jul 2024 20:37:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17863942" author="knoguchi" created="Mon, 8 Jul 2024 21:21:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Forgot to mention, I learned that disabling of&#160;tez.runtime.transfer.data-via-events.enabled done in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-5428&quot; title=&quot;Update hadoop2,3 and tez to recent versions&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-5428&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-5428&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; was necessary due to a bug reported in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TEZ-4570&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TEZ-4570&lt;/a&gt;.&#160; &#160;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;But somehow e2e tests were still not setting this flag.&#160; Moved the disabling of tez.runtime.transfer.data-via-events.enabled from TezLauncher&amp;amp;TezMiniCluster to TezDagBuilder to enforce this configuration.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17868166" author="knoguchi" created="Tue, 23 Jul 2024 19:15:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the review Rohini!&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
